<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: sigh...</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-15 12:42:02</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Yes, this robe doesn't have *that* good of stats, but they are comparable to an oracle robe.  And I don't care what anyone says, I use a lot of mana.  I have extra mana during a weak pull I'll debuff the baddie for the group, sure makes the cleric happy.  I have noticed that there are very few people that know how to pull, and quite often instead of breaking up a spawn, the people will just pull an entire room at once (EG savant to exe) and I will use a *lot* of mana on a group that isn't designed to kill things extremely fast.  If I run out of mana 2/3rds of the way through we're all in some trouble.  Mana is quite important for enchanters.<BR>
<BR>
On to the cha 5 shirt from qeynos.  I am ALL for having 200 or better charisma, as I have personally noticed a very very large difference.  But I beleive the chest piece isn't a good one sacrafice.  Lets take a level 40 character, that 25 mana is equal to about 3 int, making this a 7 int robe.  There is no way whatsoever I'm going to sac 7 int for 5 cha.  Not when you have rings where you sac 4 int for 7 cha, or wrists with 3 int for 7 cha.  There is simply no way, there are much much better places to upgrade your cha then your chest.  Neck, head, ears, wrists, fingers, you can take those all from int/mana to charisma in a much much more effecient manner.  Of course, robe of the ishva is a very good chest item, it adds a decent amount of charisma with a very nice mana addition, and I suggest wearing it for an enchanter if you can get it.<BR>
<BR>
Personally, on the male I saw this robe on I about gagged.  It looked like leather highlights on an apple green robe.  Thankfully I got to see it on a high elf female, and will get this robe if I can ever find it for sale.  I will gladly sac the 1 int from my oracle robe with being able to not be illusioned all the time because my robe is so ugly like I do now =)</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Astaron Arcanum</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-09-02 15:54:56</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>The robe drops off of the Coerced Penkeeper in Dalnir.  It's not a bad camp becuase there is a lot of stuff to pull in the area to ease the boredom.  The Spectral Crusader, and Coerced Reverant also spawn in the room.  The other drops that i know of in the room are a bunch of quest items, Serpentwood Staff, Bamboo Bo Stick, Greenwood Bo Stick, Tattered Arm Wrappings, Tattered Tomb Shroud.  I've been camping the room for 3 days now in hopes of getting a tattered tomb shroud.  I have seen everything listed drop several times but no shroud or foci.  I only stay for periods of roughly 6 hours.  However i'm not leaving til i get a shroud 8).</font></td></tr></table>
